  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study investigates if Parathyroid Tissues Anatomic Localizations Are Displaced Downward
      in Parathyroid Hyperplasia Cases or not.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Parathyroid tissues gets heavier when they become Hyperplasia. Because of this weight change,
      they change their normal anatomic positions. 125 patients who have been operated earlier will
      be included in the study.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
